HEADWORD: Mordacious
<hw>Mor*da"cious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mordax</ets>, <ets>-acis</ets>, fr. <ets>mordere</ets>,
<ets>morsum</ets>, to bite. See <er>Morsel</er>.]</ety> <def>Biting;
given to biting; hence, figuratively, sarcastic; severe; scathing.</def>
